Connected Home Full Server for mbed Device C Client Library

This project is an example of a mbed Device Server endpoint for the Connected Home Reference App, which emulates the sensors of 
a power measurement and relay node.  

To build the software, type:

make

To build the software with eDTLS library, type:

make EDTLS=YES

Usage:

connected_home_full_ipv4 [-p 8000] 
-p	port to listen on (default = 8000)
-d	mbed Device Server IPv6 address (default = ::1)
-dp mbed Device Server port number (default = 5683)

When running on the same machine as mbed Device Server, simply run:

./connected_home_full_ipv4
